#X text 1087 333 NOTES \; ---------------------------------------------------------- \; # PHASE IN FFT ENCODES POSITION IN TIME \; CONSIDE A SIGNAL IS AS ADDITION OF ITS CONSTRUCTING SINUSOID INSTEAD OF WHAT YOU SEE ON \$0-INPUT... \; AS AN EXAMPLE ITS CONSTRUCTING SINUSOID OF k0 FREQUENCY INDEX: WHEN MULTIPLIED BY EXAMINER COMPLEX SINUSOID OF FFT \, ALWAYS STARTING WITH 0 PHASE (REAL 1 \, IMAGINARY 0) \, OUTPUTS A COMPLEX NUMBER \, SHOWING REAL AND IMAGINARY PARTS. THIS BASICALLY SHOWS HOW MUCH OF THE k0 FREQUENCY INDEX IS PRESENT IN \$0-INPUT (MAGNITUDE) AND ALSO HOW IN PHASE THIS \$0-INPUT CONSTRUCTIN SINUSOID WITH FREQUENCY INDEX k0 IS WITH THE EXAMINER COMPLEX SINUSOID WHICH HAS STARTING PHASE OF 0...BASICALLY THE AMOUT OF REAL AND IMAGINARY PART OF RECOGNIZED FREQUENCY INDEX SHOWS/IS PHASE OF THE CONSTRUCTING SINUSOID OR HOW LEFT OR RIGHT IS PLACED IN TIME COMPARED TO EXAMINER COMPLEX SINUSOID... \; NOW DOING THIS FOR ALL CONSTRUCNTING SINUSOID OF A \$0-INPUT WE SEE HOW RIGHT/LEFT IS THE WHOLE SIGNAL PLACED COMPARED TO EXAMINER COMPLEX SINUSOIDS... \;;
